        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> So far we have quite a few threads running about the PoP spells. Already, have people started bitching over these. Now, I want you folks to think about something for a moment. PoP is due out when, October? Recommending changes in the spell lineup for us is absolutely worth doing. I'd love to see an upgrade to splurt and FP. However, bitching about it when the expansion is not even finished is pretty pathetic. I know about VI's track record but c'mon now.</P><P>Among the posts I have read there are 2 in which, in general, I really agreed with.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>What we don't do with dots we make up what we can with pets. Mages are finally realizing how much pets do in real world numbers. I use a pet on raids and it tends to live a long time. Shamans are gimped in range. They have 2 kinds of dots. Poison and Disease, while their epic is magic based it isn't really the exception. Guess what happens when you fight almost poison or disease immune mobs. They do no damage. All of the snakes are practically poison and disease immune. Shamans can't do crap for damage and their pet doesn't help them at all. We have how many lines of dots, poison, disease, magic and fire. That kind of diversity isn't found in any other class. This kind of envy is in the mage community too. A lot of mages hate the fact that druid nuke better than mages. But people keep posting parses of the pet doing as much damage as an SK or Paladin on the raid and sometimes as much as a warrior or a melee ranger. PLUS! they can nuke. People fail to realize the whole picture. I bet the new pets are monsters.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote><BR>-Allusha Bonebender </P><P>and</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>I don't get the arguments here, (and every other new PoP spell thread). I don't see how comparing 1 situational spell from x class to 1 situational spell from y class makes any sense in determining the viability or power of a class. Don't you really have to look at the whole picture? Like how much damage can a Nec do compared to how much damage some other class can do throughout a whole fight, (whether solo, group, or raid). Now throw in modifiers to this equation on how useful other spells/abilities are like root, snare, lev, lich, lifetap, buffs, pets, MW, DoT heals, gate, FD, corpse summons, rez, etc. </P><P>I don't feel this is such a simple equation, there is a considerable amount of data that needs to be considered. I'm not saying that Necs are/aren't less powerful... I just haven't seen any reasonable argruments here to base a conclusion on. Seems most of the arguments presented have been logic-challenged and should be ignored for their obvious lack of substance.</P><P>/shrugs Go ahead and continue all, just wanted to throw that in.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote><BR>-EQAsmar </P><P>Now, not that I agree with EVERYTHING these 2 said, but what I do know is that these 2 posted the most intelligent posts IMO thus far. What do these both have in common? Both of these individuals posted about how so many people refuse to see the entire picture and look for single instances of imbalance.</P><P>Now before the young kiddies label me as some lvl20 necro who started playing last week or as some VI rep, I'm neither. I have been on these boards for awhile now but I rarely post because there are, to say it bluntly, alot of freaking morons who bitch about what they know nothing of.</P><P>I want some new toys as much as you guys do. I am a necromancer, and I love this class to death.</P><P>My point is that we are said to have the most intelligent, unrestricted discussions around. We have some of the most incredible players in EQ here.</P><P>Let's not forget 2 things...</P><P>1. A necro is made up of more than DOTs.<BR>2. PoP is being beta tested atm and is NOT complete. The spells now might, or might not, make it into the live version. Bitching about them now instead of discussion alternates won't help. It just makes us look like the monks arguing over which race is better. =P</P><P></P><P><font color=red><BR>Vipes K`Syrix<BR>59th Defiler<BR>Prexus<BR></font id=red><BR><i>"The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, they never surrender, and they don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."</i><BR>-Nevinyrral</font></td>

