         well the fact is all that necros got was shitty dots, some shitty undead spells(wow, we will be semi useful in two zones!), shitty pet heal(this may seem cool at first, but i highly doubt it will get much use), and new pets.  im not too excited about the class pets because, well look how they fucked em in the past.  an sk pet?  great, it wont duel wield, if you think its gonna HT you are probably trippin on acid, less hp than warrior, less damage than a warrior.  personally i would prefer plain and simple, damage/hp/lifetap upgrades on pets.  watch them make the rogue pet do insane amounts of damage, but put something like 500 hp on it and say it balances the damage out. personally i would like them to leave the most powerful pets for the mages.  sure i want a strong pet, but its the mage's staple. i want a straightforward pet, not a situational one.  leave that for mages.</P><P>   the other classes have utility spells too.  that is the shittiest argument for them giving us wattered down dots.  "Now throw in modifiers to this equation on how useful other spells/abilities are like root, snare, lev, lich, lifetap, buffs, pets, MW, DoT heals, gate, FD, corpse summons, rez, etc. "   shamans get root, useful buffs, heals, slow, gate, canni, pets, armor, malo, regen, and now they are gonna get better dots as well as the incomplete heal we all know is coming.  i dont even really care about that though.  what i want is meaningful upgrades, something that would make me WANT to level to 65.  </P><P>what i would like to see, pretty much the same shit alot of people outlined:</P><P>a) lower agro on dots, or at least get rid of the DD part at the beggining of them.  for some reason wizzies can crit for 2k+ without agro but we cast a dot with 110 damage up front and we are minced meat, we didnt get a normal dot without upfront damage.  maybe they arent giving us higher damage on dots cause they know we will go down quicker than oprah on doctor phil?</P><P>b) higher damage on dots.  right now wizards are masters of damage over time on just about every encounter.  i agree wizards used to suck balls, but talk about overbalance.  they wreck shit rogue style and they still arent done crying. </P><P>hopefully we can see something along the lines of:<BR>  <BR>  splurt 2: 2600 dmg, same amount of time, low resist, 375 mana<BR>  <BR>  ebolt upgrade: 200dd, 2000dmg, 42 seconds, 500 mana (similar to FP, <BR>        hopefully easier to get)<BR>  <BR>  funeral pyre upgrade:  3000 dmg, 54 seconds, 600 mana<BR>  <BR>  cold based dot or plague upgrade: 4300dmg, 2.5 minutes, 475 mana - <BR>          the plague upgrade as it is will hardly ever get casted, <BR>          just like plague now. in its current form i dont know how <BR>          they could call it a level 65 spell.<BR>  <BR>  darkness upgrade: scratch this bullshit off the list unless you<BR>        make it damn near unresistable, and able to effect ubers<BR>  <BR>  cessation of cor upgrade: no, doesnt stack with splurt, huge agro, <BR>         why bother?<BR>  <BR>  vexing mordania upgrade: i dont think its bad. 1350 hp in 54 <BR>         seconds.  i would like to see a few hundred more hp though   <BR>         or lower the mana cost.  maybe leave damage at 1350 and make <BR>         it heal more like 1700? unresistable! </P><P>i think that with these numbers we could do meaningful damage on just about every encounter in game without being overpowered.  there is no way we could stack all these dots without getting eaten/ going oom extremely quick.  so its balanced out but we would have a nice arsenal to choose from.</P><P>c) utility/ other spells:<BR>  undead mez: this is nice in that it has no recast, 30% mem blur and lasts 30 seconds.  would be nicer if it lasted a bit longer.  another option would be to make it mez all, make it shitty, slightly better than ST 10% mem blur, 20 second duration. that way if we want to mez we can mem both and it will still be hard.  the undead only spells are cool, but for things that dont generally have to do with necros, like DD, slow, charm. i guess mez can fit in there, but we already have a mez all spell. either way, i dont end up mezzing much anymore as it is, and undead mez is highly situational, neither way would add much power, just decent utility.<BR>   <BR>   pet buff:  looks nice<BR>   <BR>   pet heal: whatever, its cool, would rather see a shadowbond  <BR>        upgrade, like a 1000 hp transfer<BR>   <BR>   lifetap: would love to see a new deflux.  666 lifetap, 350 mana, 3 <BR>        second cast time. also i would love to see the EE component <BR>        removed from trucidation.  maybe increase the mana cost to <BR>        like 425 on it.<BR>   <BR>   a nice undead DD, zefeers and maybe MW upgrades, and better <BR>        upgrade on the shielding spells than what they gave would all <BR>        be icing.</P><P>d) make focus items that increase damage per tick.  or make extended affliction increase it by more than one tick, or make some AA for necros for dots like wizards have with crits.  it can be done.</P><P>i think these things would make the necro community happy, without overpowering us.  of course all this depends on how much they end up giving to other classes.  they could give us all this but then give wizards a 10k dmg lure DD for 400mana and we still end up looking shitty.  thats the thing about balance, people say "dont compare to other classes"  but in order for there to be balance you HAVE TO compare to other classes.  you think if wizards best nuke was still ice comet and rogues couldnt backstab and shamans couldnt heal that any necros would be complaining? its all relative, and right now, relatively speaking, our shit stinks. its been proven that verant listens to the bitching.  they are not just gonna realize how bad these spells suck if we are all quiet and cross our fingers and hope.  i never hoped my way through anything.  we get vocal now or get shafted later.</P><P></P><P></P><P